HEADWORD: Enchylemma
<hw>En`chy*lem"ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <?/ to pour in + <?/ anything received.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld>
<def>The basal substance of the cell nucleus; a hyaline or granular
substance, more or less fluid during life, in which the other parts of
the nucleus are imbedded.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

